# DaySprings – Ruby on Rails 

---

## Day 1 – Ruby & Rails Basics

### Ruby
- Dynamically typed, open-source language
- Everything is an object
- Latest version: Ruby 3.x
- Follows SOLID principles (except Interface Segregation)

### Rails
- Web framework built using Ruby
- Latest version: Rails 8.x

### Important Points
- Version management: RVM / RBENV
- Install Rails:
  gem install rails
- Rails provides MVC structure and boilerplate code

### Create Rails Project
- rails new project_name
- rails new project_name --api
- rails generate scaffold

### Commands
- ruby --version
- rails --version
- rails new ProjectName

---

## Day 2 – Database & Scaffold

### Database Commands
- rails db:create
- rails db:migrate
- rails db:seed

### Scaffold
- Generates model, controller, views, routes
- rails generate scaffold Customer name:string email:string

### database.yml
- Stores database configuration
- Incorrect values cause db errors

### Rails Console
- rails console

---

## Day 3 – Rails Concepts & Structure

### Features
- Syntactic Sugar
- Convention over Configuration
  - Model → singular
  - Controller → plural

### config Folder
- database.yml
- routes.rb
- application.rb
- environment.rb
- environments (dev, test, prod)

### db Folder
- migrate/
- schema.rb
- seeds.rb

---

## Day 4 – app Folder & Ruby Basics

### app Folder
- controllers
- models
- views
- javascript
- mailers
- jobs

Best Practice:
- Thin Controllers
- Thick Models

### Data Types
- String
- Integer
- Float
- Symbol
- Boolean
- nil

### Variables
- Local
- Global ($)
- Instance (@)
- Class (@@)
- Constant (UPPERCASE)

---

## Day 5 – Methods & Type Casting

### Methods
- Auto return value
- Use return only if needed

### Comments
- Single line: #
- Multi-line: =begin =end

### Type Casting
- to_i
- to_s
- to_f

### Product Scaffold
rails generate scaffold Product name:string description:text price:decimal stock:integer is_active:boolean

### Data Insertion
- UI
- Database tools
- seeds.rb
- Rails console

---

## Day 6 – Loops & Collection Methods

### Loops
- for
- while
- loop do
- until

### Collection Methods
- each
- select
- reject
- map / collect

### Notes
- Methods do not change array by default
- Use ! to modify
- Boolean methods end with ?

### Rails Data Method
- pluck

Example:
Product.limit(10).pluck(:price)



Correct:
Product.where(is_active: true).limit(10)

---

